        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"numpy/numpy\",\n      \"path\": \"numpy/_core/fromnumeric.py\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"pandas-dev/pandas\",\n      \"path\": \"pandas/core/arrays/_mixins.py\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"scipy/scipy\",\n      \"path\": \"scipy/stats/_stats_py.py\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"numpy/numpy\",\n      \"path\": \"numpy/_core/fromnumeric.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"sum\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"pandas-dev/pandas\",\n      \"path\": \"pandas/core/arrays/_mixins.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"NDArrayBackedExtensionArray\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"scipy/scipy\",\n      \"path\": \"scipy/stats/_stats_py.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"describe\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"numpy/numpy\",\n      \"path\": \"numpy/_core/fromnumeric.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"sum\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"pandas-dev/pandas\",\n      \"path\": \"pandas/core/arrays/_mixins.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"NDArrayBackedExtensionArray\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"scipy/scipy\",\n      \"path\": \"scipy/stats/_stats_py.py\",\n      \"symbol\": \"describe\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Scientific computing data flow traces across three architectural layers:\\n\\n1. Array Computation Layer (NumPy): The canonical entry point for array-level aggregation on raw ndarray objects is the `sum` function in `numpy/_core/fromnumeric.py` (line 2305). This function provides the primary user-facing interface for array aggregation operations. It accepts array-like inputs and uses `_wrapreduction` to delegate to ufunc reduction methods, demonstrating NumPy's core aggregation architecture.\\n\\n2. Data Structure Layer (Pandas): The class that wraps a NumPy ndarray as a pandas extension array is `NDArrayBackedExtensionArray` in `pandas/core/arrays/_mixins.py` (line 92). This class extends both `NDArrayBacked` and `ExtensionArray`, maintaining an internal `_ndarray` attribute that stores the NumPy array. It provides the abstraction layer allowing pandas to wrap and extend NumPy arrays with additional functionality.\\n\\n3. Scientific Computation Layer (SciPy): The `describe` function in `scipy/stats/_stats_py.py` (line 1444) is a comprehensive statistical function that accepts numpy arrays and pandas Series (via array_like) as inputs. It performs multiple statistical calculations including mean, variance, skewness, and kurtosis, demonstrating how SciPy leverages NumPy arrays and pandas data structures for statistical analysis.\\n\\nThe data flow demonstrates how raw NumPy arrays are aggregated through canonical functions, wrapped in pandas extension arrays for tabular data manipulation, and finally consumed by SciPy statistical functions for advanced analysis.\"\n}\n",
